        "client_msg_id": "e27193fc-58b5-4901-b36d-2f270e9defa6",
        "text": "I am begging to think about what is history in this model. You could generate a UUID every save and include the prior version to form a linked list, but this seems kinda fragile if you lose a file in the middle. Or maybe keep a list of content hashes within the file so the history is inside the doc, but you might not necessary have hard copies of everything (but you can search your filesystem for those hashes perhaps), or maybe you really keep all the operations for full replayability (could be nasty size wise if we consider a file upload as a recorded operation), nice thing with keeping the operations is you can make a cool animation of the evolution over time. Should it just have git in there so we don't reinvent the the wheel and allow merging across different histories?",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
